<h2 id=3D"id-02.SD:TransactionListing(Customer&amp;StaffPortal)-SecurityAsp=
ects">Security Aspects</h2>
<p>The Galaxy application security is per below.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Authentication</strong>: It will be handled with Ping Federate =
using PKCE flow.</li>
<li><strong>Authorisation</strong>: The authenticated user is entitled to s=
ee the transactions for all accounts stored in the Mesh secrets (tactical s=
olutions).</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-02.SD:TransactionListing(Customer&amp;StaffPortal)-ErrorHandli=
ng">Error Handling</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-02.SD:TransactionListing(Customer&amp;StaffPortal)-Summary:">S=
ummary:</h3>
<p>For Feb-release, the below error codes should be handled by the UI:</p>
<ul>
<li>Bad Request Error</li>
<li>Server Error</li>
<li>Timeout Error</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Read more here: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au=
/x/xUrNXw" class=3D"" rel=3D"nofollow">https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.a=
u/x/xUrNXw</a></strong></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-02.SD:TransactionListing(Customer&amp;StaffPortal)-Data&amp;In=
formationModel">Data &amp; Information Model&nbsp;&nbsp;</h2>
<p>All mappings between UI and each service layer listed in below.</p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Transactions listing UI-Experien=
ce API Mapping: <a class=3D"" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au=
/x/tFfNXw" rel=3D"nofollow">https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/x/tFfNXw<=
/a></span></li>
<li>Experience API- Source Systems Data Mapping: <a href=3D"https://conflue=
nce.srv.westpac.com.au/x/g87_Vw" class=3D"" rel=3D"nofollow">https://conflu=
ence.srv.westpac.com.au/x/g87_Vw</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-02.SD:TransactionListing(Customer&amp;StaffPortal)-Operational=
Impacts">Operational Impacts</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-02.SD:TransactionListing(Customer&amp;StaffPortal)-Logging:"><=
span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Logging:</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The recommended logging framework =
to use for API development is<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=3D"external=
-link" href=3D"http://www.slf4j.org/" rel=3D"nofollow">SLF4J</a><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">, and it has<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/plugins/ser=
vlet/search?q=3Dproject%3AWDP+slf4j" rel=3D"nofollow">widest adoption</a><s=
pan style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>across WDP platform =
APIs as of March 2020: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/dis=
play/WDPIPAAS/Logging+Framework+-+Java" rel=3D"nofollow">Read more</a> .</s=
pan></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">As a general concern, we should ma=
sk any <strong><u>PII</u></strong> data or <u><strong>sensitive</strong> </=
u>identifiers.&nbsp;</span></p>
<h3 id=3D"id-02.SD:TransactionListing(Customer&amp;StaffPortal)-Security:">=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Security:</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">In addition to client side data va=
lidation, server side validation should also be performed to ensure that th=
e correct request is being received from the UI. The&nbsp;<a class=3D"exter=
nal-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/UI-WWW1/rep=
os/wdp-ui-expcommon/browse/packages/bootstrap" rel=3D"nofollow">@wdpui/comm=
on-middleware</a><span>&nbsp;</span>package (part of @wdpui/common-bootstra=
p) provides some middleware to enhance the security of experience APIs. The=
 common bootstrap is required to be used in all projects unless an exemptio=
n is received from ISG.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpa=
c.com.au/display/MESH/6.3.8+Security" rel=3D"nofollow">Read more here</a>.<=
/span></p>
